   <body>
      <context>
         <note>Bottom cable entry: Route the power cables through
the conduit box in the bottom of the UPS cabinet. Top
cable entry: Route the preinstalled power cables in the top entry
cabinet through the left side and into the UPS cabinet.</note>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the two plates in the bottom of the UPS cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/50_kva_connect_power_cables_remove_plates_120mm_0000104238.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         translate="no"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Connect the equipment grounding conductor to the ground
busbar.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/50_kva_connect_power_cables_connect_ground_cable_120mm_0000104279.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         translate="no"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Connect the input cables to the input busbars (L1, L2,
L3 (N)).</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>Only connect input N in single mains systems.</note>
               <fig expanse="page">
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/50_kva_connect_power_cables_to_terminals_120mm_0000104237.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         translate="no"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Connect the bypass cables to the bypass busbars (L1, L2,
L3, N).</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>Only connect bypass cables in dual mains systems.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Connect the output cables to the output busbars (L1, L2,
L3, N).</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Connect the battery cables (+,-, ground) to the battery
busbars (+, -) and to the ground busbar.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>Route battery cables from adjacent battery cabinets
through the left side panel of the UPS cabinet.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
      </ol>
